evan heit uc merced relations between memory and reasoning department of psychology stanford university department of psychology search psychology web site evan heit uc merced relations between memory and reasoning navigation people research and experiments education and training events related programs resources job opportunities about us user login sunet id login home evan heit uc merced relations between memory and reasoning speaker evan heit uc merced location jordan hall building 420 room 050 in this talk i will give an overview of three lines of work addressing relations between memory and reasoning the first two lines of work take concepts and modeling tools from memory research and apply them to unsolved classic problems in reasoning research how induction and deduction are related and what is the best theory of the belief bias effect the third line of work directly compares memory and reasoning judgments on the same set of visual stimuli aiming to predict reasoning from memory and develop a common model for both abilities public access not open to the public date and time friday 14 january 2011 3 15pm stanford home contact us maps and directions department of psychology jordan hall building 01 420 stanford university 450 serra mall stanford ca 94305 tel 650 725 2400 fax 650 725 5699
